HEADWORD: Mesaticephalic
<hw>Mes`a*ti*ce*phal"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<ets><?/</ets> midmost + E. <ets>cephalic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the ratio of the length to the breadth of
the cranium a medium one; neither brachycephalic nor
dolichocephalic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesaticephalous</ent>⟦br⟧
